Figure 3b shows the XRD pattern of H@TNAs-1. Almost all the diffraction peaks of H@TNAs-1 could be well indexed to anatase TiO2. It was worth to note that the abnormal extremely sharp peaks were assigned to anatase (004) planes, which indicated that the H@TNAs-1 may possess the crystal orientation of {001} facets. To determine the crystal growth of anatase, the texture refinement was performed by using whole powder pattern fitting (WPPF) method, based on March-Dollase function (1) (W(α)), ellipsoid model [47].1Wα=rn2cos2αn,h+rn−1sin2αn,h−3/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
